                                                                                                               Stock boss tips on social duty
  - XIMB holds 17th annual convocation          OUR CORRESPONDENT                           Shekhar Datta, the chief of the Bombay Stock Exchange, addresses the 17th annual convocation of XIMB. Picture by Sanjib Mukherjee                                        
	Bhubaneswar, March 27: The 17th annual convocation of Xavier Institute of Management, Bhubaneswar (XIMB), Orissas premier B-school, today saw 344 students receiving their diplomas.         
	Honchos from trade and industry, academia, distinguished invitees, proud parents and excited students rubbed shoulders on this occasion.         
	This year, the convocation saw 119 PGDM students, 61 PGDM (rural management) students, 47 executive PGDM students and 116 PGCBM students and one FPM student being awarded their respective graduating diplomas.         
	Chief guest for the evening Shekhar Datta, the chairman of Bombay Stock Exchange, exhorted students to remember their obligation to the society.        
	Speaking on the occasion Datta said: As you go on in your careers, remember that you have an obligation to the society, which has provided you the opportunity to excel in your chosen field.         
	As beneficiaries we owe a debt to the society that gave us this chance to bring out the best in ourselves. So, even as you scale pinnacle of professional success, never forget your obligation to the less fortunate in the country.         
	Datta further said: There are two things needed to enable one to lead a fulfilling life  the wisdom to know the right path and the courage to follow it.         
	On this day, two toppers with the highest scores among all of this years passouts  Soumya Gayatri and Puspamitra Prusty  were awarded the CM Kandoi Gold Medal along with a cash prize of Rs 10,000 and Rs 5,000, respectively.         
	The NTPC medal went to Soumya Gayatri for scoring the highest among all the girls and to Suchita Dikshit for being the HRM topper.         
	The Ravi Sharma Memorial Gold Medal for the best all-rounder went to Tushar Bagla.                                                                                                                                                                           
